      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-08-09T21:08:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don’t think we ever want to do this. What you’re now calling “force” is an operation that should only ever be applied to single crash reports. That’s what should happen if the user is on about:crashes and decides “I want to upload this one report, but I don’t want to enable uploads for all reports.”\n\nWe wouldn’t want to bring all of these reports back to life and make them eligible for upload in one fell swoop. We certainly wouldn’t want to do that while circumventing the user’s upload-enabled preference.",
      "revId": "96974a129a585fd073be8d3ae8d7598385e46545",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
